# Patterns and conventions

## Naming

- API handlers: app/server/api/<segments>/<name>.<method>.ts (e.g., register-entry.post.ts)
- Tests mirror feature area:
  - API: app/server/api/__tests__/*
  - Services: app/server/services/**/__tests__/*
  - Forecast: app/server/services/forecast/**/__tests__/* (plus TS test-runner)
  - App libs: app/lib/__tests__/*
  - E2E: app/tests/e2e/**
- Prisma migrations under app/prisma/migrations/YYYYMMDDHHMMSS_<name>/migration.sql
- Monetary values are Decimal; never use JS floating point for persisted money. When rounding in code, use bankers-rounding utilities (app/lib/bankers-rounding.ts)

## Validation and error handling

- Prefer Zod schemas in app/schema/* for payload parsing (see schema/zod.ts and usage in handlers)
- Wrap handlers with withErrorHandler or use handleApiError utilities to normalize responses
- Use accountAccess.ts and requireAdmin.ts for authorization gates
- For 3rd-party errors (Plaid), normalize via plaidApiError.ts

## Services and side effects

- Place domain logic in app/server/services/*
- If writes impact derived data (summaries, caches, forecasts), ensure you update via services or enqueue recalculation jobs (recalculateQueue)
- For integration operations, record audit or job logs (recordAdminAudit.ts, recordIntegrationJobLog.ts, recordPlaidSyncLog.ts)

## Forecast engine

- Treat server/services/forecast/* as a module boundary
- Data flow typically goes: DataLoaderService → ForecastEngine (orchestrates AccountRegisterService, ReoccurrenceService, RegisterEntryService, TransferService, LoanCalculatorService, etc.) → DataPersisterService
- Reuse types (services/forecast/types.ts) and utility rateLimiter (lib/rateLimiter.ts)
- Keep tests updated; there are extensive unit/integration/regression suites

## Encryption-sensitive data

- Fields annotated with /// @encrypted or /// @encryption:hash(...) in app/prisma/schema.prisma must be treated carefully
- Use generated prisma/reencrypt/* when migrating/re-encrypting
- For Plaid access tokens and identifiers, use server/lib/plaidAccessTokenCrypto.ts and never log raw values

## Adding or changing API endpoints (safe checklist)

- Create files under app/server/api/... with proper <method> suffix
- Validate inputs (Zod) and enforce access checks early
- Prefer services for logic; keep handlers thin
- Add unit/integration tests under app/server/api/__tests__
- If user-facing, wire composables/stores (useAPI/useAppFetch; update stores/* as needed)
- Update E2E tests when UI flows change

## Schema changes (safe checklist)

- Edit app/prisma/schema.prisma; run prisma migrate dev (local) and generate
- Update seed or reencrypt code as needed (reencrypt is generated)
- Review microservice/prisma/schema.prisma — update if the migration surface is affected by your change
- Run pnpm test and review API/service tests for breakage
- Update .env.example when new env vars are required; update .deploy templates if secrets/config change in prod/staging

## Code style and CI

- TypeScript enforced with ESLint; see .cursor/rules/10-code-style-and-ts.mdc for detailed per-project guidance
- Pre-commit hooks run TruffleHog and block committing .env files
- Conventional commit style is encouraged (see CONTRIBUTING.md)

## When to enqueue vs. inline execute

- Inline for short, idempotent operations with predictable latency (<100ms)
- Enqueue when:
  - Integration calls (Plaid/Alchemy) or long DB work
  - Potential retries required
  - You need observability via IntegrationJobLog or queue introspection

## Time and timezone

- Tests and services often assume TZ=UTC; respect getTodayFromTestDate.ts and DateTimeService usage in forecast code
